node.title: Astros pull Justin Verlander from second spring start with sore triceps - ESPN
node.description: Houston Astros ace Justin Verlander was pulled from his spring training start against the New York Mets after two innings Sunday and will undergo tests, the team said.

node.title: Iowa State stuns Baylor, snaps Lady Bears' 58-game Big 12 win streak - ESPN
node.description: Iowa State hands Baylor its first Big 12 loss since 2017, a 57-56 decision that snapped the Lady Bears' conference run of dominance at 58 games.

node.title: Giannis Antetokounmpo to sit out two Bucks games after spraining knee - ESPN
node.description: Giannis Antetokounmpo has a minor joint capsule strain of his left knee and will not play in the remaining two games of the Milwaukee Bucks' road trip, the team announced.

node.title: Ohio State product Cardale Jones benched in first quarter of XFL game after string of poor performances - USA TODAY
node.description: Ohio State product Cardale Jones was benched in the first quarter of the D.C. Defenders' game Sunday. Tyree Jackson replaced him.
